The net reproductive rate (R0), that is the cumulative summation of lxmx, is age-specific net maternity which is the product of lx (age-specific survival rate) and mx (age-specific fecundity), and was calculated as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_{0} = \sum\limits_{x = 0}^{\infty } {l_{x} m_{x} }$$\end{document}R0=∑x=0∞lxmx

The intrinsic rate of natural increase (rm), where T is generation time:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
